Core Principles
Backend is brand-agnostic. No brand column, no brand filtering, no brand-aware logic in any service, model, or API route.

Backend services are task-specific. Each service does ONE thing well:

AI Cake Studio Service = generates cake images, period.
It doesn't know if the caller is CrossFriend or some future brand.
It only cares: is this customer authenticated? do they have credits? are they rate-limited?
Frontend owns feature gating. Which features are shown on which domain is 100% a frontend decision. Backend exposes capabilities; frontend decides who sees them.

Customer accounts are shared. One Medusa customer table serves both storefronts. A customer who signs up on CrossFriend could theoretically log in on PranaJiva too (same email/phone → same account). Credits, history, and leads are tied to the customer ID, not to a brand.

Data is not partitioned by brand. The ai_generations table stores ALL generations regardless of which frontend triggered them. If in the future PranaJiva also uses image generation, the same table stores those too. Filtering/display is frontend's job.

What This Means for AI Cake Studio Backend
DO: Build a generic "AI image generation for cakes" service
DO: Authenticate via Medusa customer JWT (standard _medusa_jwt cookie)
DO: Track credits per customer (not per brand)
DO: Rate-limit per customer (not per brand)
DO: Store generations per customer (not per brand)
DON'T: Add any brand field to tables
DON'T: Check which domain the request came from
DON'T: Filter responses by brand
DON'T: Have different behavior for different storefronts_
AI Cake Studio Service — Specialization
The AI Cake Studio backend service is specialized for cake image generation. This means:

Prompt engineering is optimized for cake/bakery imagery
The system prompt sent to the AI provider will include cake-specific context (tiers, fondant, buttercream, decorations, etc.)
The generation metadata captures cake-specific fields (occasion, style, flavor, weight, tiers)
The leads system is designed for baker handoff (not generic e-commerce)
Price estimation factors are cake-specific (weight, tiers, shape, eggless, etc.)
But it does NOT:

Know about CrossFriend branding
Apply brand-specific rules
Behave differently based on caller identity beyond auth + credits

